    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - TRANSFER CASES - DISASSEMBLE - LOWER SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>LOWER SHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1303433">Figure 33</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1303433" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303433.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 33. Lower Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove shift unit from front of case as described in
                <hotlnk document="s13034_8.xml" xrefid="x1303401">Shift Unit</hotlnk>
                section and refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303434">Figure 34.</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303434" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303434.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Remove Shift Unit</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn unit over and remove locking nut, washer and end yoke or companion flange from rear
                output shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303435">(Figure 35)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303435" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303435.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Remove Locking Nut, Washer, End Yoke From Rear Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove six (6) bolts and lockwashers from output bearing cap flange and remove bearing cap
                and gasket
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303436">(Figure 36)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303436" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303436.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 36. Remove Output Bearing Cap Flange, Bearing Cap, And Gasket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For unit that does not use a rear output, remove snap ring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a driver to remove output shaft
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303437">(Figure 37)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303437" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303437.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 37. Remove Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Care should be taken to prevent damage to threads or allowing shaft to fall to floor.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove spacer and press off bearing
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1303438">(Figure 38)</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1303438" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg13/G1303438.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 38. Remove Spacer And Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing by sliding to large opening.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide output gear to large opening and remove.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
